  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tajikistan: Reforms on Access to Judicial Decisions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To remove legislative limitations on public access to judicial decisions in line with international standards; 2) To enhance transparency, accountability of economic courts and predictability of judicial decisions.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Judges and employees of the SEC; Badakhshan Region (GBAO) Economic Court; Khatlon Region Economic Court; Sught Region Economic Court; Dushanbe City Economic Court.Indirect stakeholders:Individuals and partiesto the cases; Legal entities, entrepreneurs, domestic and international commercial companies;Authorities, state institutions of Tajikistan and foreign countries.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to provide assistance to the Tajik stakeholders to review and amend legislation and regulations on public access to judicial decisions by preparing a report identifying laws, regulations and other normative provisions that limit access to judicial decisions, and drafting recommendations on how to align them with international best practice.</narrative>
  </description>
